entry.title: Kyiv Faces Lengthier Blackouts as Russia Assaults Ukraine Grid
entry.content: Kyiv residents are facing prolonged blackouts, after Russian airstrikes again hit the Ukrainian electric system overnight, further degrading the country’s ability to keep the lights on.

entry.title: Inside the Secret Prisoner Swap That Splintered the U.S. and China
entry.content: The detention of a Chinese executive to stand trial in the U.S. provoked a standoff between global rivals and opened an acrimonious new era. “You are lapdogs of the United States.”
